<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="1310" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1310">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.77/136.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador and
                                    the American Consuls at Nogales, Ciudad Juárez, Ciudad Porfirio
                                    Díaz, Nuevo Laredo, and Matamoros</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Identic telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 14, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In order to prevent any possible misunderstanding of the Department’s May
                            13, you are informed that the data requested therein was ordered
                            obtained by the President personally, and is desired for the purpose of
                            securing employment in the United States for these idle men.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>